<font color="#FF0000">NEW START</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 10 11:12:34 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I have made it through the Fattening Moons and now see the Moon when the Grass turns Yellow.  Soon I will see the Moons when horses grow long hair... I will see the Moons when birds fall frozen from the trees.<br>
Following this I will witness Kiwani owapi, a new awakening in Ina Maka, the Mother Earth.  Where old things have died, new things will be born.  Some things will neither die or be born again, but simply go around the circle again.<br>
It is called Wanisugna or owani wasu ognaka, meaning life within the shell... creative force... seed.<br>
It is called Wanagi, spiritual self.<br>
I must stop warfare in my mind that my spirit can do wanaspi, surround the buffalo, make meat for mental norrishment. I will say, Ta ta iciya wo, lie down as if dead and relax your vigilence.  I will think on Wahpani iciya wo, to give everything away, as does Ina Maka, the Mother Earth when the White Giant brings wasu, the snow and falling ice.<br>
I will watch new life come from different seeds and maybe I will answer the question, once more, Tuwe miye he, Who am I?<br><br>

